{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f9a0b1c2-af-nexus-2026-v2",
    "name": "Amobear Nexus \u2014 AppsFlyer APIs v2",
    "description": "Postman collection v2 cho AppsFlyer API integration v\u00e0o Amobear Nexus.\n\nDoc reference: 128 \u2014 AppsFlyer Integration\n\n## Key Update v2\n- Folder 00: App List API \u2014 l\u1ea5y danh s\u00e1ch t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 apps\n- Folder 07: Master API ALL APPS \u2014 `app_id=all` cho Nexus pipeline\n  - 4 request t\u00e1ch theo KPI type (LTV, Retention, Activity, Cohort)\n  - Kh\u00f4ng mix KPI types trong c\u00f9ng 1 call\n\n## Authentication\n- Pull API: `api_token` in query param\n- Master API / Cohort API / App List: `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n\n## Rate Limits\n- Pull API: 10 calls/min per app\n- Master API: 40 calls/min\n- Cohort API: 5 calls/min\n\n## \u26a0\ufe0f Master API `app_id=all` notes:\n- L\u1ea5y ALL apps trong 1 call \u2014 kh\u00f4ng c\u1ea7n loop per-app\n- currency=preferred ch\u1ec9 work n\u1ebfu t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 apps c\u00f9ng currency\n- N\u1ebfu apps kh\u00e1c currency \u2192 d\u00f9ng USD (default)\n- T\u00e1ch 4 calls: LTV, Retention, Activity, Cohort (kh\u00f4ng mix \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c)\n- Date range max 90 ng\u00e0y\n- Data freshness: T+1 \u0111\u1ebfn T+2",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://hq1.appsflyer.com",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "api_token",
      "value": "YOUR_API_V2_TOKEN_HERE",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "AppsFlyer API V2 Token \u2014 Dashboard \u2192 your email \u2192 API Tokens"
    },
    {
      "key": "app_id",
      "value": "com.amobear.puzzlegame",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Single app: Android=com.package / iOS=idXXX. Or use 'all' for Master API"
    },
    {
      "key": "from_date",
      "value": "2026-04-01",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "to_date",
      "value": "2026-04-07",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "nexus_webhook_local",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000/api/webhooks/appsflyer",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 \u2014 App List API",
      "description": "L\u1ea5y danh s\u00e1ch t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 apps trong AppsFlyer account.\nD\u00f9ng \u0111\u1ec3 build mapping table cho Nexus.\n\nAuth: Bearer token in header.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "0.1 List All Apps",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/mng/apps?limit=1000&offset=0",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "mng",
                "apps"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "1000"
                },
                {
                  "key": "offset",
                  "value": "0"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "L\u1ea5y danh s\u00e1ch apps. Max 1000 per page, paginate via offset.\n\nResponse fields per app: id (app_id), name, platform, currency, time_zone.\n\n**Nexus use:** Daily sync \u2192 config.appsflyer_app_mapping table.\nCheck total_items in meta \u2192 if > 1000, paginate."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "0.2 List Apps (Page 2)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/mng/apps?limit=1000&offset=1000",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "mng",
                "apps"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "1000"
                },
                {
                  "key": "offset",
                  "value": "1000"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Page 2 n\u1ebfu c\u00f3 > 1000 apps."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "07 \u2014 Master API: ALL APPS (Nexus Pipeline)",
      "description": "\ud83d\udd25 CORE REQUESTS cho Nexus daily pipeline.\n\n`app_id=all` \u2192 1 call l\u1ea5y T\u1ea4T C\u1ea2 apps.\nT\u00e1ch 4 requests v\u00ec LTV, Retention, Activity, Cohort KPIs KH\u00d4NG MIX \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Rate limit: 40 calls/min.\n\u26a0\ufe0f Date range max 90 ng\u00e0y.\n\u26a0\ufe0f currency=preferred ch\u1ec9 work n\u1ebfu t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 apps c\u00f9ng currency \u2192 n\u1ebfu kh\u00f4ng, b\u1ecf param (default USD).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "7.1 ALL APPS \u2014 LTV KPIs (install-day revenue, cost, ROI)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid,geo,c,af_adset,af_ad&kpis=installs,cost,revenue,roi,arpu_ltv,average_ecpi,clicks,impressions,ctr,conversion_rate,sessions,loyal_users,loyal_users_rate,total_revenue,total_cost&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid,geo,c,af_adset,af_ad"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,cost,revenue,roi,arpu_ltv,average_ecpi,clicks,impressions,ctr,conversion_rate,sessions,loyal_users,loyal_users_rate"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "\ud83d\udd25 PRIMARY Nexus sync call \u2014 ALL apps, ALL LTV KPIs.\n\nGroupings: app_id \u00d7 install_time \u00d7 pid \u00d7 geo \u00d7 campaign \u00d7 adset \u00d7 ad.\n\n**Confirmed working KPIs:**\ninstalls, clicks, impressions, ctr, conversion_rate\ncost, average_ecpi (CPI)\nrevenue, arpu_ltv, roi\nsessions, loyal_users, loyal_users_rate\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Protect360 KPIs (blocked_installs) require separate premium subscription.\nDo NOT include them unless Protect360 is enabled on your account.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f If response too large: remove af_ad grouping, or split date range."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.2 ALL APPS \u2014 LTV KPIs (lightweight \u2014 cho daily sync)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid,geo&kpis=installs,cost,revenue,roi,average_ecpi,sessions,loyal_users_rate&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid,geo"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,cost,revenue,roi,average_ecpi,sessions,loyal_users_rate"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Lightweight version cho daily recurring sync.\nB\u1edbt groupings (no adset/ad) \u2192 response nh\u1ecf h\u01a1n, nhanh h\u01a1n.\n\nD\u00f9ng cho Hangfire daily job \u2014 app_id \u00d7 date \u00d7 media_source \u00d7 geo."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.3 ALL APPS \u2014 Retention KPIs (D1, D3, D7, D14, D30)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid,geo&kpis=installs,retention_day_1,retention_day_3,retention_day_7,retention_day_14,retention_day_30&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid,geo"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,retention_day_1,retention_day_3,retention_day_7,retention_day_14,retention_day_30"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "\u26a0\ufe0f SEPARATE CALL \u2014 Retention KPIs kh\u00f4ng mix v\u1edbi LTV KPIs.\n\nD1/D3/D7/D14/D30 retention by app \u00d7 date \u00d7 media_source \u00d7 geo.\nRetention = % users still active on day N.\n\n**Nexus Gold mapping:**\n- retention_day_1 \u2192 app_ua_daily.d1_retention\n- retention_day_7 \u2192 app_ua_daily.d7_retention\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f retention_day_7 data cho ng\u00e0y X ch\u1ec9 available X+7 ng\u00e0y sau.\nN\u00ean sync T-7 to T-1 cho retention data."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.4 ALL APPS \u2014 Activity KPIs (DAU, MAU, sessions, revenue, uninstalls)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid&kpis=activity_average_dau,activity_average_mau,activity_average_dau_mau_rate,activity_sessions,activity_revenue,activity_arpu,activity_uninstalls&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,sessions,loyal_users,revenue,cost,uninstalls"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Activity KPIs \u2014 sessions, revenue, uninstalls grouped by app \u00d7 install_time \u00d7 pid.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Activity KPIs in Master API use the SAME field names as LTV KPIs.\nThere is NO 'activity_' prefix. The difference is in how data is aggregated:\n- LTV = by install date (cumulative)\n- Activity = by event date (but Master API always uses install_time grouping)\n\nFor event-date based activity, use Aggregate Pull API instead."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.5 ALL APPS \u2014 Cohort Revenue (D7, D14, D30, D60, D90)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid,geo&kpis=installs,cost,cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_14_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_60_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_90_total_revenue_per_user&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid,geo"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,cost,cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_14_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_60_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_90_total_revenue_per_user"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cohort revenue per user at D7/D14/D30/D60/D90.\n\n**Nexus Gold mapping:**\n- cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user \u2192 app_ua_daily.ltv_d7_usd\n- cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user \u2192 app_ua_daily.ltv_d30_usd\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f cohort_day_0 NOT supported in Master API.\n\u26a0\ufe0f D90 data only available for installs \u2265 90 days ago.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f ERROR 416: Happens when date range is too narrow for cohort data.\nCohort D7 needs at least 7 days of data AFTER install date.\nIf from=to=2026-04-04, D7 cohort data won't exist yet.\n\nFIX: Set from_date at least 30 days in the past.\nExample: from=2026-03-01&to=2026-03-15 for D7/D14 cohort data."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.6 ALL APPS \u2014 Cohort ROAS + Sessions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid&kpis=installs,cost,cohort_day_7_roas,cohort_day_30_roas,cohort_day_7_sessions,cohort_day_30_sessions&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,cost,cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_14_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cohort revenue per user at D7/D14/D30.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Master API cohort KPIs only support: cohort_day_X_total_revenue_per_user\ncohort_day_X_roas and cohort_day_X_sessions do NOT exist in Master API.\nFor ROAS calculation, use calculated_kpi formula instead.\nFor detailed cohort data, use the Cohort API (POST endpoint)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.7 ALL APPS \u2014 Conversion Funnel KPIs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid&kpis=installs,blocked_installs,blocked_installs_rate,detection_installs,detection_installs_rate&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,clicks,impressions,ctr,conversion_rate"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Conversion funnel: clicks \u2192 impressions \u2192 installs \u2192 sessions.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Protect360 KPIs (blocked_installs, detection_installs) require premium subscription.\nIf you have Protect360 enabled, add: blocked_installs,blocked_installs_rate\n\nThis request uses standard LTV KPIs as fallback."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.8 ALL APPS \u2014 Core UA Performance",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid,geo&kpis=installs,af_purchase_unique_users,af_purchase_event_counter,af_purchase_sales_in_usd&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid,geo"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,revenue,sessions,loyal_users"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Core UA performance: installs, cost, revenue, sessions by app \u00d7 install_time \u00d7 pid \u00d7 geo.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f In-app event KPIs in Master API:\nFormat is NOT {event_name}_unique_users. Event-level data is embedded in the\nstandard revenue/sessions KPIs or retrieved via Pull API raw data.\n\nFor event-level breakdown, use Pull API in-app events report instead."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.9 ALL APPS \u2014 Calculated KPI (Custom ROAS D7, Payback Period)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/master-agg-data/v4/app/all?from={{from_date}}&to={{to_date}}&groupings=app_id,date,pid&kpis=installs,cost,revenue&calculated_kpi_roas_d7=(cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user-average_ecpi)/average_ecpi&calculated_kpi_ltv_cac_ratio=cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user/average_ecpi&format=csv",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "master-agg-data",
                "v4",
                "app",
                "all"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "from",
                  "value": "{{from_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "to",
                  "value": "{{to_date}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "groupings",
                  "value": "app_id,install_time,pid"
                },
                {
                  "key": "kpis",
                  "value": "installs,cost,revenue,average_ecpi,cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user,cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user"
                },
                {
                  "key": "calculated_kpi_roas_d7",
                  "value": "(cohort_day_7_total_revenue_per_user-average_ecpi)/average_ecpi"
                },
                {
                  "key": "calculated_kpi_ltv_cac_ratio",
                  "value": "cohort_day_30_total_revenue_per_user/average_ecpi"
                },
                {
                  "key": "format",
                  "value": "csv"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Custom calculated KPIs. Base KPIs MUST be included in kpis param.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f Calculated KPI formulas reference other KPIs that must also be in the kpis list.\nThe formula KPIs (average_ecpi, cohort_day_X_total_revenue_per_user) must be\nexplicitly listed in kpis= even if you only want the calculated result.\n\nIf this still errors, try with fewer KPIs first to identify which ones your plan supports."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "7.10 ALL APPS \u2014 JSON format (for programmatic parsing)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{api_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
